quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  18,21,"And thus We caused them to be discovered, that they{1}would know that the promise of Allah{2}is true and that of the Hour there is no doubt. As they were disagreeing with each other about their affair, they said, “Build over them a structure.” Their Lord knows better about them. Those who prevailed over their affair{3}said, “We will set up over them a mosque{4}.”",footnotes:1:The people of the city who discovered them.|2:A grammatical shift from 1st person to 3rd person.|3:Literally ‘those who overcame (the others) in their affair’.|4:The Arabic word is masjidwhich literally means ‘a place for prostration’.
  18,22,"Some will say, “Three, their fourth being their dog.” And some will say, “Five, their sixth being their dog,” —guessing at the unknown. And some will say, “Seven, and their eighth being their dog.” Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “My Lord knows better of their exact number”. None knows<i class=""s"">(the reality about) </i>them except a few. So enter<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>not into controversies concerning them except on a matter that is clear, and do not consult any of them{1}about them.",footnotes:1:The People of the Scripture.
  18,23,"And never say about anything, “I will do that tomorrow”"
  18,24,"without<i class=""s"">(saying) </i>, “God willing.” And remember your Lord if you forget<i class=""s"">(to say it) </i>and say, “Hopefully my Lord will guide me to something nearer to prudence than this.”"
  18,25,"And they remained in their cave for three hundred years, adding nine."
  18,26,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “Allah knows better how long they remained; to Him belongs the hidden realm of the heavens and the earth. How clearly He sees and how finely He hears! They have no guardian apart from Him, and <span class=""h"">He does<sup foot_note=""80471"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">not associate</span>anyone in His judgment.”"
  18,27,"And read<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>what was revealed to you from the Scripture of your Lord; none can change His words, and you will find no refuge apart from Him."
